al tools used in the sculpture, on the other. In addition to providing a fascinating and cogent consideration of medieval beliefs about salvation and redemption, this book also lays the groundwork for a long overdue examination of the performative and textual in relationship to sculpture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aSermons, French. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  a13th century.  aamiens.  acathedral.  acatholic church.  acovenant.  adoctrine.  aeurope.  afrench catholicism.  agothic architecture.  ahistory.  amedieval beliefs.  amedieval religion.  amedieval sermon.  amedieval.  amother of god.  anonfiction.  anotre dame.  aoration.  aoratory.  apicardy.  apreach.  apreacher.  apriest.  aredemption.  areligion.  areligious experience.  arepentance.  asaint mary.  asaints.  asalvation.  ascripture.  asculpture.  asermon.  asinner.  aspirituality.  avirgin mary.  avisual culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093007040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520930070423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520930070/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles